# ===============================================================
# GAPS — Information the ontology cannot represent
# ===============================================================
#
# 1. PERSONS / MAKERS (no mi:Person or mi:Luthier class):
#    - Andrea Amati, Stradivari family, Guarneri family, Guadagnini,
#      Jacob Stainer, Gasparo da Salo, Giovanni Paolo Maggini,
#      Matteo Goffriller, Montagnana, etc.
#    - Performers: Ole Bull, Jimi Hendrix, Itzhak Perlman,
#      Joe Venuti, Stephane Grappelli, Jean-Luc Ponty,
#      Vanessa-Mae, Lindsey Stirling, etc.
#
# 2. COMPOSITIONS (no mi:Composition class):
#    - Danse Macabre (Saint-Saens), Contrasts (Bartok),
#      Paganini Violin Concerto No.1, Mystery Sonatas (Biber),
#      Symphonie Fantastique (Berlioz), The Planets (Holst), etc.
#
# 3. LOCATIONS / PROVENANCE (no mi:Place class):
#    - Brescia, Cremona, Italy, Austria, Venice, Lyon, etc.
#
# 4. TIME PERIODS (no temporal class):
#    - "16th century", "Baroque era", "Golden Age", "1716", etc.
#
# 5. INSTRUMENT PARTS (no mi:InstrumentPart class):
#    - Bridge, soundpost, tailpiece, chinrest, fingerboard, pegbox,
#      scroll, f-holes, purfling, nut, endpin, etc.
#
# 6. PLAYING TECHNIQUES (no mi:Technique class):
#    - Pizzicato, col legno, arco, spiccato, martele, tremolo,
#      vibrato, harmonics, double stops, scordatura, etc.
#
# 7. BOW as separate entity (no mi:Bow class):
#    - The bow is extensively described but has no dedicated class.
#
# 8. TUNING DETAILS beyond what mi:hasScale can express:
#    - Iranian Dastgah-specific tunings (e.g. Dastgah-e Esfahan E-A-E-A)
#    - Specific maqam systems
#    - A=440 Hz reference pitch
#
# ===============================================================
